Without this, tools and examples packages are installed on System
domain.

comments.message: Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

Patch Set 1:

Without a manifest properly defined in the spec file the files will get installed into the floor domain. They will run in the System domain unless started by programs running in the User domain. What domain are you using?

What is the rule for this? I am having similar problems with other packages that install applications and are supposed to run as 'app' user. This application then spawns others but it gets a permission denied error.

Using the manifest with '_' domain solves the problem.

subject: PTREL-546 fix: enable wayland build
commitMessage:
PTREL-546 fix: enable wayland build

The display server based on X or Wayland, is now a choice of different profile in Tizen 3.0.
Basically and consistently, two macros were used "with wayland" and "with x".
Below summarize the combination of the macros:

    | wayland |  x  | meaning
    |---------------------------
    |   0     |  1  | pure X11 platform(no wayland)
    |   1     |  0  | pure wayland platform (no X11)
    |   1     |  1  | wayland but X compatibility
    |   0     |  0  | no X and no wayland

This method unifies the meaning and usage. Deploy this method to elementary package.

Change-Id: I761ef5a9b03493fe7e867282d4d3cd2a812d7482
